FibonacciHeap
public interface PriorityQueue<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

A priority queue based on T implementing Comparable on T.

This interface represents a min-priority-queue, i. e. for any two elements e1 and e2 if e1.compareTo(e2) < 0, e1 will be first.

Author:
Rosario Raulin

Method Detail

min

T min()
Returns the smallest element in this priority queue without modifying the queue. That is, two successive calls to this method will return the same element unless extractMin() or decreaseKey() is called.

Returns:
the smallest element or null, if queue is empty
See Also:
extractMin(), decreaseKey(de.raulin.rosario.heaps.PQNode)

extractMin

T extractMin()
Return the smallest element in this priority queue and removes it. The next call to extractMin() or min() will NOT return the same element but the second smallest element in this priority queue.

Returns:
the smallest element or null, if queue is empty
